.TH "TILDR\-PLUGINS" "1" "2026" "Tildr" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tildr\-plugins \[em] file manager plugins for Tildr
.SH SYNOPSIS
Tildr provides native integration with popular Linux file managers
through plugins, allowing you to manage files directly from the context
menu without using the terminal.
.SH DESCRIPTION
Both plugins expose the same three operations via a \f[B]Tildr\f[R]
submenu in the context menu:
.TP
\f[B]Add\f[R]
Add the selected file(s) to the Tildr repository and replace them with
symlinks.
.TP
\f[B]Unlink\f[R]
Remove the symlink(s) from \f[CR]$HOME\f[R] without touching repository
content.
.TP
\f[B]Restore\f[R]
Move the file(s) back from the repository into \f[CR]$HOME\f[R] and
remove the symlinks.
.PP
Multiple file selection is supported in both plugins.
All selected files are passed to the Tildr command in a single
invocation.
.SH NAUTILUS
Integration with Nautilus (GNOME Files) is done via
\f[B]nautilus\-python\f[R], a Python extension API that allows adding
custom items to the context menu.
.SS Requirements
One of the following packages must be installed:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]python\-nautilus\f[R] \[em] Arch Linux
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]python3\-nautilus\f[R] \[em] Debian, Ubuntu, Linux Mint
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]nautilus\-python\f[R] \[em] Fedora
.SS Features
.IP \[bu] 2
Context menu submenu \f[B]Tildr → Add / Unlink / Restore\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Supports single and multiple file selection
.IP \[bu] 2
Available only for files and symlinks, not directories
.IP \[bu] 2
Only appears when inside the user\[cq]s home directory
(\f[CR]\[ti]/\f[R])
.SS Manual Installation
.IP
.EX
mkdir \-p \[ti]/.local/share/nautilus/python\-extensions
curl \-fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/orbitbits/tildr/main/tools/plugins/nautilus/tildr.py \[rs]
  \-o \[ti]/.local/share/nautilus/python\-extensions/tildr.py
nautilus \-q
.EE
.SS Plugin Location
\f[CR]\[ti]/.local/share/nautilus/python\-extensions/tildr.py\f[R]
.SH DOLPHIN
Integration with Dolphin (KDE) is done via \f[B]KIO Service Menus\f[R],
a \f[CR].desktop\f[R] file mechanism that adds custom actions to the
context menu.
No additional dependencies are required beyond Dolphin itself.
.SS Features
.IP \[bu] 2
Context menu submenu \f[B]Tildr → Add / Unlink / Restore\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Supports single and multiple file selection
.IP \[bu] 2
Available for files and symlinks
.SS Manual Installation
.IP
.EX
mkdir \-p \[ti]/.local/share/kio/servicemenus
curl \-fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/orbitbits/tildr/main/tools/plugins/dolphin/tildr.desktop \[rs]
  \-o \[ti]/.local/share/kio/servicemenus/tildr.desktop
.EE
.PP
No restart is required.
Dolphin picks up new service menus automatically.
.SS Plugin Location
\f[CR]\[ti]/.local/share/kio/servicemenus/tildr.desktop\f[R]
.SH AUTOMATIC INSTALLATION
Both plugins are installed automatically by the Tildr installer script
when the respective file manager is detected on the system:
.IP
.EX
curl \-fsSL https://orbitbits.github.io/tildr/linux.sh \f[B]|\f[R] sh
.EE
.PP
If the file manager is not installed at the time of Tildr installation,
the plugin can be installed manually at any time using the commands
above.
